[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer fuzzing run detected a Server-Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m issue of medium [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseverity. During the processing of a ZIP archive in [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`CompressZipFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`, the code attempted to open a socket to an [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntrusted destination [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`jazze.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The SSRF sanitizer in the Jazzer framework [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflagged this network connection as a security violation.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Observed  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The fuzzer input triggered a call chain that ultimately invoked [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`java.net.Socket.connect` and `java.net.URL.openStream`, leading to an attempted [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconnection to `jazze.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m`. This activity was intercepted by [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrf`, resulting in a `FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The issue is identified as Server-Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Untrusted data is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfluencing outbound network requests, which can lead to unauthorized access to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternal services, exfiltration of sensitive data, or other unintended interactions[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith external or internal endpoints.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important Observations  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The exception originates in the Jazzer sanitizer class [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ServerSideRequestForgery` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m71[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m127[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m rather than in the fuzzer harness [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mitself.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The code path involves standard Java networking [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Socket`, `HttpClient`, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`HttpURLConnection`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and is triggered by the Apache Commons Compress `ZipFile` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor and central directory parsing routines.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`CompressZipFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m serves as an entry [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoint, feeding crafted inputs into the ZIP-processing logic, but is not the root [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcause.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code Areas to Investigate  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile` constructors and [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcentral-directory parsing methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39mespecially around line [0m[1;36m1552[0m[39m for [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`readCentralDirectoryEntry`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Any code that resolves URLs or initiates network connections based on ZIP [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive contents or metadata.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Integration points between the ZIP-processing logic and networking APIs [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`java.net.Socket`, `HttpURLConnection`, `URL.openStream`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. The server-side request forgery checks in [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.ServerSideRequestForgery` to understand [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhow inputs are validated and where bypasses may occur.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`CompressZipFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to map how input data propagates into[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe vulnerable code path and to identify additional test cases that may trigger [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimilar behavior.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1330[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mwordBbuf.rewind[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1331[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mIOUtils.readFully[0m[1;39m([0m[39marchive, wordBbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1332[0m[39m:            sig = [0m[1;35mZipLong.getValue[0m[1;39m([0m[39mwordBuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1333[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1334[0m[39m:        return noUTF8Flag;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1335[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/archivers/zip/ZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:21[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m71[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m21[0m[39m:import java.io.BufferedInputStream;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m22[0m[39m:import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m23[0m[39m:import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m24[0m[39m:import java.io.Closeable;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m25[0m[39m:import java.io.EOFException;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m26[0m[39m:import java.io.File;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m27[0m[39m:import java.io.IOException;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m28[0m[39m:import java.io.InputStream;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m29[0m[39m:import java.io.SequenceInputStream;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m:import java.net.URL;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m:import java.nio.ByteBuffer;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m:import java.nio.ByteOrder;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m:import java.nio.channels.FileChannel;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m:import java.nio.channels.SeekableByteChannel;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m:import java.nio.charset.Charset;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m:import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m37[0m[39m:import java.nio.file.Files;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m38[0m[39m:import java.nio.file.OpenOption;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m39[0m[39m:import java.nio.file.Path;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m40[0m[39m:import java.nio.file.StandardOpenOption;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m41[0m[39m:import java.util.Arrays;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m42[0m[39m:import java.util.Collections;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m43[0m[39m:import java.util.Comparator;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m44[0m[39m:import java.util.EnumSet;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m45[0m[39m:import java.util.Enumeration;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m46[0m[39m:import java.util.HashMap;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m47[0m[39m:import java.util.LinkedList;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m48[0m[39m:import java.util.List;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m49[0m[39m:import java.util.Map;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m50[0m[39m:import java.util.Objects;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m51[0m[39m:import java.util.stream.Collectors;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m52[0m[39m:import java.util.stream.IntStream;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m53[0m[39m:import java.util.zip.Inflater;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m54[0m[39m:import java.util.zip.ZipException;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.EntryStreamOffsets;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.compress.compressors.bzip2.BZip2CompressorInputStream;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:import [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.commons.compress.compressors.deflate64.Deflate64CompressorInputStream;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.compress.compressors.xz.XZCompressorInputStream;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m:import [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.commons.compress.compressors.zstandard.ZstdCompressorInputStream;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.compress.utils.BoundedArchiveInputStream;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.compress.utils.BoundedSeekableByteChannelInputStream;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.compress.utils.IOUtils;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.compress.utils.InputStreamStatistics;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.compress.utils.SeekableInMemoryByteChannel;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.io.Charsets;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.io.FilenameUtils;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.io.build.AbstractOrigin.ByteArrayOrigin;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.io.build.AbstractStreamBuilder;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.io.function.IOStream;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:import org.apache.commons.io.input.BoundedInputStream;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Root Cause & Objective**  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The SSRF stems from this block in `ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1551[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m1559[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which unconditionally opens a URL based on untrusted ZIP entry [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomments. Our goal is to preserve ZIP‐reading functionality while preventing ANY [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnetwork calls by default, and optionally allow them under an explicit, opt-in flag.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Add an “allowRemoteComments” Flag**  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile`, introduce a private [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinal field:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private final boolean allowRemoteComments;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Create a new primary constructor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor extend the deepest existing one[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtakes this flag:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath p, [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     Charset encoding, [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     boolean useUnicodeExtraFields, [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     boolean allowRemoteComments[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m existing constructor logic [0m[33m...[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         this.useUnicodeExtraFields = useUnicodeExtraFields;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         this.allowRemoteComments     = allowRemoteComments;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m continue initialization[0m[33m...[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Modify all existing public constructors to chain to the new signature, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpassing `false` for `allowRemoteComments`.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      For example:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mf.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;35mCharset.defaultCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               DEFAULT_USE_UNICODE_EXTRA_FIELDS, [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This preserves backward compatibility: existing code paths set [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteComments = false` with no behavior change except disabling remote [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfetch.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Guard the Network Fetch**  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In `readCentralDirectoryEntry`, replace:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream is = new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m fetch remote content[0m[33m...[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m swallow[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   with:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteComments[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream is = new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m fetch remote content[0m[33m...[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m swallow[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m else: leave commentString unchanged [0m[1;39m([0m[39mURL literal[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This ensures **no** untrusted network calls when `allowRemoteComments == false`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **API Documentation & Javadoc**  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Update the Javadoc for the new constructors, explaining that remote comment [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfetching is disabled by default and can be enabled by passing `true` to [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteComments`.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Document that URL‐prefixed comments remain as literal text when the feature is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdisabled.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Preserve Core ZIP Functionality**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All size, offset, encoding, extra‐field and local‐header logic remains [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntouched.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only the optional post-processing of entry comments is gated.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other code paths or utility methods are modified, ensuring minimal impact.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Testing & Compatibility**  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests continue to pass: they see identical comment strings [0m[1;39m([0m[39mminus [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremote fetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m because `allowRemoteComments` defaults to `false`.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If downstream users require remote comment resolution, they can instantiate [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile` with the new flag enabled in their own test code or applications.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No modifications to fuzz harness, external libs, or utility functions.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Security Outcome**  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By default, untrusted ZIP archives can no longer trigger outbound HTTP/S [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconnections, completely closing the SSRF vector.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Offering an explicit, opt-in mechanism maintains flexibility for legitimate [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muse cases without compromising security.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This pattern aligns with “secure by default” principles and preserves the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal intent of remote comment fetching for advanced users.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35mCompressZipFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCompressZipFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:30[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: b38823cc610751ee[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer invocation of the `CompressZipFuzzer` triggered a [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium: Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry` processed a ZIP comment that began with “http” [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand opened a remote connection. In response, a patch was attempted against [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.java` to introduce a boolean [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflag [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`allowRemoteComments`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m guarding remote comment fetching, add new [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructors, and adjust related field declarations. After applying the patch, the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuild failed during Java compilation with multiple “illegal start of expression” [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand related syntax errors in `ZipFile.java`.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Jazzer’s SSRF sanitizer flagged a security issue at runtime: during [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`fuzzerTestOneInput` of `CompressZipFuzzer`, `ZipFile` code invoked `new [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, causing a connection to `jazze.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace showed the vulnerability detection in [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrfSocket`, propagating through standard Java [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnetworking APIs into Apache Commons Compress’s ZIP reader.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `ZipFile.java`, the patch:  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Removed or commented out the original `SeekableByteChannel [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseekableByteChannel;` declaration.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Introduced two new `private final boolean` fields: `useUnicodeExtraFields` and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteComments`.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Added two new public constructors taking `Path`, `Charset`, [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`useUnicodeExtraFields`, and optionally `allowRemoteComments`, replacing the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeprecated channel-based constructor.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Modified the code that reads the central directory comment [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1548[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto wrap the remote-fetch logic in an `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteComments && [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m …[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` guard.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBuild Log After Patch  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During `mvn compile`, errors in `ZipFile.java` were reported at lines [0m[1;36m881[0m[39m, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m903[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m904[0m[39m:  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • “illegal start of expression”  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • “illegal start of type”  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • “<identifier> expected”  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • “illegal character: ‘#’”  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • “; expected”  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- These errors indicate malformed Java syntax introduced by the patch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mduplicate [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield initializations, misplaced braces or annotations, or stray characters[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The top of `ZipFile.java`: verify that new field declarations do not conflict [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith existing ones [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., duplicate `useUnicodeExtraFields` definitions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The placement and syntax of the added constructors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m873[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m903[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: ensure [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproper method signatures, parameter lists, and exception declarations.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The comment-reading block [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1548[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: check that the [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteComments` guard and URL logic are enclosed correctly within existing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod scope.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any related builder or factory classes that reference the old constructors or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfields, to understand how the class is instantiated elsewhere.[0m                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39minside of the central directory which will not be available when the argument is[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m779[0m[39m:     * set to [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@code true[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m. This includes the content of the Unicode extra [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield, so setting [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@code[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m780[0m[39m:     * ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m to [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@code true[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m means [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@code [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39museUnicodeExtraFields[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m will be ignored effectively.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m781[0m[39m:     * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mp[0m[39m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m782[0m[39m:     *[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m783[0m[39m:     * @param file                  the archive.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m784[0m[39m:     * @param encoding              the encoding to use for file names, use [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnull for the platform's default encoding[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m785[0m[39m:     * @param useUnicodeExtraFields whether to use InfoZIP Unicode Extra Fields[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mif present[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to set the file names.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m786[0m[39m:     * @param ignoreLocalFileHeader whether to ignore information stored inside[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe local file header [0m[1;39m([0m[39msee the notes in this method's Javadoc[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m787[0m[39m:     * @throws IOException if an error occurs while reading the file.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m788[0m[39m:     * @since [0m[1;36m1.19[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m789[0m[39m:     * @deprecated Use [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link Builder#[0m[1;35mget[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m790[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo resolve the SSRF vulnerability while fixing the Java syntax errors, we must [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreapply a corrected, cohesive patch against the initial codebase. The root cause is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man unguarded call to `new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`readCentralDirectoryEntry`, combined with an improper patch that introduced [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduplicate/misplaced field declarations and malformed constructors. Our strategy [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrestores syntactic correctness, preserves all existing functionality [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeprecated constructors[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and centralizes a new `allowRemoteComments` flag.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Add a new field at the top of `ZipFile.java` next to the existing [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`useUnicodeExtraFields` declaration:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Locate the core fields [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m695[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Insert:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       private final boolean allowRemoteComments;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This new field tracks whether remote comments are permitted.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Extend the private core constructor to accept and assign the new flag:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Signature before:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       private [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       String channelDescription,[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       Charset encoding,[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       boolean useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       boolean closeOnError,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       throws IOException[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Revised signature [0m[1;39m([0m[39madd `boolean allowRemoteComments` as last parameter[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       private [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       String channelDescription,[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       Charset encoding,[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       boolean useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       boolean closeOnError,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       boolean allowRemoteComments[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       throws IOException[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • In the constructor body, before populating entries, assign:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       this.useUnicodeExtraFields = useUnicodeExtraFields;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       this.allowRemoteComments    = allowRemoteComments;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • All existing logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpopulating directories, closing on error[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Update every constructor chaining into this core constructor to forward a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault `false` for the new flag:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Deprecated constructors for `File` and `SeekableByteChannel`:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Change calls like[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchannel, desc, charset, true, closeOnError, ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       to[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchannel, desc, charset, true, closeOnError, ignoreLocalFileHeader, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Change calls like[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mfile.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, encoding, useUnicodeExtraFields, ignoreLocalHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       to[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mfile.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, encoding, useUnicodeExtraFields, ignoreLocalHeader, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • This preserves backward compatibility—clients who use deprecated APIs continue[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto have remote comments disabled.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Introduce two new public constructors for `Path` + `Charset`:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • One taking `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath p, Charset charset, boolean useUnicodeExtraFields[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls through with `[0m[33mallowRemoteComments[0m[39m=[0m[35mfalse[0m[39m`.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Another taking `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath p, Charset charset, boolean useUnicodeExtraFields, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean allowRemoteComments[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that invokes the core constructor and sets all [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfields.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Follow the same pattern as existing Path-based constructors: open the channel,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39massign class fields, call `[0m[1;35mpopulateFromCentralDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, handle cleanup on [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Guard remote comment fetching in `readCentralDirectoryEntry`:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Locate the block:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       String commentString = [0m[1;35mentryEncoding.decode[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomment[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m… [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Change to:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteComments &&[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • This disables URL-based comment loading unless the flag is explicitly set.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Extend the `Builder` API to configure `allowRemoteComments`:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • In `ZipFile.Builder` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnear line [0m[1;36m140[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       private boolean allowRemoteComments = false;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Add a fluent setter:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       public Builder [0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteComments[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean allow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           this.allowRemoteComments = allow;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return this;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Modify `[0m[1;35mget[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` so its constructor call becomes:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualChannel,[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          actualDescription,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          [0m[1;35mgetCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          closeOnError,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          allowRemoteComments[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • All other builder methods remain unchanged, preserving existing behavior and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefaults.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Validate no duplicate or misplaced fields remain:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Remove any stray redefinitions of `useUnicodeExtraFields` or accidental [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremoval of `seekableByteChannel` in the builder.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Ensure consistent indentation and ordering of modifiers [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`private final` vs. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`private`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m. Test compilation and behavior:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Run `mvn compile` to confirm no “illegal start of expression/type” or [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstray-character errors.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Run existing unit tests to verify no regressions.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Run the SSRF fuzzer to confirm that remote-comment opening is blocked by [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault and that explicitly enabling `allowRemoteComments` restores the original [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By centralizing the new flag in the core constructor and propagating it through [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall entry points, we avoid malformed signatures and duplicated fields.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Wrapping the URL-loading logic preserves functionality for users opting in while [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblocking SSRF by default.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Extending the Builder ensures a clean, discoverable API for advanced users [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout touching harness or test code.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Careful parameter ordering and default-values maintain backward compatibility [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith all deprecated constructors.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This approach addresses the compilation errors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mduplicate and misplaced field [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclarations[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and resolves the runtime SSRF issue in one coherent patch.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn SSRF issue was discovered when the ZIP archive reader fetched remote ZIP-file [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomments starting with “http” or “https,” triggering a Jazzer [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium` on `Socket.connect`. A patch was attempted to introduce[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma new `allowRemoteComments` flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefaulting to `false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throughout [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile.Builder`, the various `ZipFile` constructors, and the comment-reading [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic—guarding the remote fetch behind this flag. After applying the patch, the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuild fails with two compiler errors:  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. A duplicate constructor signature for `[0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile, String, boolean, boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. An incompatible type error where a `Charset` is passed where a `String` is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpected.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A Jazzer fuzzing run caused a [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium: Server Side Request [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mForgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` exception.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace shows the failure in `ServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrfSocket`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreached via `java.net.Socket.connect` when [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocesses an entry comment beginning with “http”.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer input was a specially crafted ZIP archive that set its central [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory comment to a URL, leading the ZIP reader to open a network connection.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey observations  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The vulnerability arises in the ZIP comment handling code.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The SSRF sanitizer flags any outbound socket calls based on untrusted data.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The relevant code is in `ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry`, where it reads the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomment buffer, converts it to a string, and, if it starts with “http”[0m[35m/[0m[39m“https,” [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mopens a `new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `ZipFile.Builder`, added  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  private boolean allowRemoteComments = false;[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m780[0m[39m:     * ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m to [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@code true[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m means [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@code [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39museUnicodeExtraFields[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m will be ignored effectively.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
